## On the clarity of Appendix A.3

The reviewer notes that A.3 is terse and hard to follow on first reading. We
agree. \rev{In addition to promoting the core argument to Section 3.2 (above),
A.3 has been expanded with a worked example at $p = 3$ showing explicitly how a
single coordinate update perturbs every other sufficient statistic, and how the
latent layer removes that dependence. We have also added a schematic contrasting
the two computational graphs --- $p$ sequential network evaluations versus one
batched evaluation --- which we hope makes the point visible before the algebra.}

